# Incident Report — IR-2026-001

**Analyst:** Muna  
**Date:** June 15, 2026  
**Severity:** High  
**Status:** Resolved  

---

## what happened

detected an SSH brute force attack against my Oracle Linux VM during a homelab exercise. the attack came from my Kali Linux VM and generated 312 failed login attempts in under 2 minutes. my Splunk detection rule caught it almost immediately and auto_triage.py automatically enriched the source IP, made a triage decision, and logged the case — no manual intervention needed. no successful logins occurred.

