## what i'd do differently in a real environment

| priority | action | why |
| --- | --- | --- |
| high | deploy fail2ban — auto-block after 5 failed attempts | stops the attack before it hits 300+ attempts |
| high | disable password SSH, enforce key-based auth only | brute force literally can't work without passwords |
| high | auto_triage escalation for external IPs | if source was external with high abuse score, script should auto-block at firewall |
| medium | tighten firewall to only allow SSH from trusted IPs | reduces exposure surface |
| medium | lower alert threshold from 5 to 3 attempts | catches it even faster |
| low | audit all default credentials across every service | default creds were how my CCDC environment got compromised too |

