## summary

the detection worked exactly as expected — two layers caught the attack. splunk fired the alert and auto_triage.py handled the triage automatically without me touching anything. no access was gained, the logs gave me everything i needed, and the case was documented end to end.

the auto_triage decision of NEEDS_REVIEW was correct for a homelab context. in a production SOC with an external attacker IP, the abuseipdb enrichment would likely return a HIGH risk score, the decision would flip to TRUE_POSITIVE, and the recommended action would be immediate firewall block + Tier 2 escalation.

